    "created_at": "2024-08-08T11:37:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-08-08T11:37:55Z",
    "body": "Thanks for sharing buddy!!\r\nAfter checking out your fish fn i got this for zsh\r\n```zsh\r\nfunction shell() {\r\n    # Initialize empty arrays for package names and options\r\n    ps=()\r\n    os=()\r\n\r\n    # Loop through all the arguments\r\n    for p in \"$@\"; do\r\n        if [[ \"$p\" != --* ]]; then\r\n            # If not an option, add it to the package names array\r\n            ps+=(\"nixpkgs#$p\")\r\n        else\r\n            # If it is an option, add it to the options array\r\n            os+=(\"$p\")\r\n        fi\r\n    done\r\n\r\n    # Construct the command\r\n    cmd=\"SHELL=$(which zsh) IN_NIX_SHELL=\\\"impure\\\" nix shell ${os[*]} ${ps[*]}\"\r\n    echo \"Executing \\`$cmd\\`...\"\r\n    \r\n    # Execute the command\r\n    eval $cmd\r\n}\r\n```",
